                                          @NonNull

                                   throws java.lang.AssertionError
        Abbreviates an input String from its first character up to the character denoted by idx.
        Parameters:
        str - The string to abbreviate
        idx - The index of the character that ends the substring generation. If we call it n, the substring generated is s[0,...n-1].
        Returns:
        str, appropriately abbreviated.
        Throws:
        java.lang.AssertionError - if idx is less than 1, or if str has zero length.
        See Also:
        String.substring(int, int)
